{
  "texts": [
    "They can be of 3 types: interactive with visual feedback, interactive simulators along with haptic feedback and non-interactive [56].",
    "The literature shows that when compared to control methods, residents who received VR simulation education outperformed those in the control group [57].",
    "Orthopedics is highly dependent on spatial understanding of the musculoskeletal system, which may be considerably improved by using VR.",
    "According to a survey of orthopedic residents, VR simulation training improved their arthroscopy skills, and they believed the skills obtained through VR will transfer to the operation theatre [101].",
    "Previous research has shown that VR simulator training could enhance basic arthroscopy skills and reduce surgery time of residents [102,103]."
  ]
}